==Abstract==

This IIP repurposes the transaction input sequence number field to encode relative lock-times. A relative lock-time specifies the minimum age of the input (in blocks or time) before the transaction can be included in a block. It is adapted from BIP 68 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

Absolute lock-times (IIP-6) are useful but have limitations:

* Require knowing the exact future block height or time
* Cannot express "wait N blocks after funding"
* Inefficient for payment channels (must update locktime)

Relative lock-times enable:

* '''Payment Channels''': Revocable outputs with fixed delay
* '''Lightning Network''': Commitment transaction delays
* '''Atomic Swaps''': Timeout relative to contract creation
* '''Vaults''': Spending delay after initiation

==Specification==

===Sequence Number Encoding===

The 32-bit nSequence field is interpreted as follows when the disable flag is not set:

<pre>
Bit 31 (DISABLE_FLAG):     If set, nSequence is ignored for relative lock-time
Bit 22 (TYPE_FLAG):        If set, interpret as time-based; otherwise block-based
Bits 0-15 (VALUE):         The lock-time value

  31                 22                  16                   0
  |                  |                   |                    |
  [D][------------][T][----------------][       VALUE        ]
   |       unused    |       unused              |
   |                 |                           |
   DISABLE_FLAG     TYPE_FLAG             16-bit value
</pre>

===Lock-Time Calculation===

'''Block-based''' (TYPE_FLAG = 0):
<pre>
required_height = input_height + VALUE
</pre>

'''Time-based''' (TYPE_FLAG = 1):
<pre>
required_time = input_MTP + (VALUE * 512)
</pre>

Where:
* input_height = height of block containing the UTXO
* input_MTP = median time past of that block
* 512 = granularity in seconds (~8.5 minutes)

===Consensus Rules===

For each input where DISABLE_FLAG is not set:

<pre>
if TYPE_FLAG == 0:
    # Block-based
    if current_height < input_height + VALUE:
        return INVALID
else:
    # Time-based
    if current_MTP < input_MTP + (VALUE * 512):
        return INVALID
</pre>

===Constants===

<pre>
SEQUENCE_DISABLE_FLAG   = (1 << 31)  # 0x80000000
SEQUENCE_TYPE_FLAG      = (1 << 22)  # 0x00400000
SEQUENCE_LOCKTIME_MASK  = 0x0000ffff
SEQUENCE_GRANULARITY    = 512        # seconds
</pre>

===Maximum Values===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Type !! Maximum Value !! Real Duration
|-
| Blocks || 65535 || ~91 days (at 2-min blocks)
|-
| Time || 65535 × 512 || ~388 days
|}

==Rationale==

===Why Sequence Numbers?===

The nSequence field was originally intended for transaction replacement but was never widely used. Repurposing it:
* Requires no new transaction fields
* Maintains backward compatibility
* Enables per-input relative locks

===512-Second Granularity===

The 512-second granularity:
* Allows ~388 days maximum with 16 bits
* Provides sufficient precision for most use cases
* Aligns with Bitcoin for cross-chain compatibility

===Disable Flag===

The disable flag allows:
* Opt-out of relative lock-time semantics
* Compatibility with legacy sequence number uses
* RBF signaling (sequences < 0xffffffff-1)

==Backwards Compatibility==

Transactions with nSequence = 0xffffffff are unaffected (disable flag set).

This is a soft fork: old nodes will accept transactions that new nodes reject.

==Interaction with Other IIPs==

* '''IIP-6 (CLTV)''': Absolute and relative locks can be combined
* '''IIP-8 (CSV)''': Script-level enforcement of relative locks

